I trained Ricky how to smoke. I can train him to shoot a poison dart. No jury would convict us ’cause people love monkeys.
Excuse me. Have you considered that your intelligence might be the very thing causing your dilemma?
What do you think Ricky over here would do if an interloper encroached on his territory?
You’re being too literal. My point is, he would not meekly surrender to the rules, and neither should you.
Yes, dirty. Dirty, dirty, dirty. Which brings me to our next order of business. (Kisses him)
I hope you don’t take what I’m about to do as a comment on what we just did. (Runs to bathroom and vomits)
It most assuredly is not.
Yes. I also found a Korean man’s business card tucked into my cleavage. What happened last night?
Sheldon?
Okay. Don’t really know where we go from here.
Terrific. Thank you. (Noise of Ricky in background) They were out of menthols! Get off my back! Not easy living with a temperamental little primate.
I must say, Penny, this is great fun.
Until I met you and Bernadette, my trips to the bathroom had been entirely focused on elimination. Now they have a delightful social aspect.

You okay in there, bestie?

She always this crabby when she urinates?
And I’ll be right by your side.

Your trusting nature coupled with your teeny-tiny body. You wouldn’t last a minute on the Serengeti.

You are, with hair that smells like strawberries. And we’re going to use that to our advantage.

Oh, my metatarsal are barking.

Thank you. Did you know that women wear high heels to make the buttocks and breasts more prominent?
Look.

I heard it at the mall, when I was shopping with my girlfriends, ’cause, you know, that’s kind of my life now. Have a good night. Try not to ogle my caboose as I walk away.
I don’t understand. Is this a way to break in new shoes?
Good news: the wildebeest is in the curry.
Bernadette is with Priya and Leonard. Message received. Commence operation “Priya Wouldn’t Wanna Be-ya.”

How do you want to handle it?

It’s indeed admirable. Although, it is microbiology.

Now push your third finger along the ridge of the shoulder blade, making a small rotation as you do so.
You should feel a small node-like object rolling back and forth along the bone.

dialogue: I should’ve gotten a lawyer.

That’s nothing. In ninth grade, the girls put Rogaine in my hand lotion. Within six months, the nicknames began to fly. I think the one that hurt the most was Gorilla Fingers Fowler.
Come on, no one ever gave anyone mean nicknames or picked on them or put gum in their hairy knuckles so the school nurse had to use peanut butter to get it out?
Did Kathy Geiger laugh?
Who would have thought Fuzzy Fingers Fowler is best friends with a bully?
Shh. That’s how you wind up in a cornfield.
I think your mistake is doing it over the phone. If they could look into your eyes, they’d melt.
Perhaps you could assuage your guilt through altruism. Which word’s tripping you up? Assuage or altruism?
I never doubted you.
There’s Habitat for Humanity, building houses for the poor.
How about donating some of your clothes?
I don’t think Mother Teresa… Oh, that is adorable.
You were right, a whole new load.
Check it out, Bernadette, suede boots, your size.
What is it, the fuzz?
I was gleefully following you to a life of crime, looking forward to the day we might be cell mates. I don’t know about Bernadette.

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 12 – The Shiny Trinket Maneouvre
dialogue: Oh, yes. Our relationship agreement specifies that the second Thursday of every month, or the third Thursday in a month with five Thursdays, is date night.

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 12 – The Shiny Trinket Maneouvre
dialogue: How was your day?

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 12 – The Shiny Trinket Maneouvre
dialogue: Sounds like you hit the ground running. I have a bit of good news myself. My most recent paper on how a cooperative long-term potentiation can map memory sequences in dendritic branches made the cover of Neuron.

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 12 – The Shiny Trinket Maneouvre
dialogue: That’s nice. Anyway, I’ve been dreaming of this day for a long time.

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 12 – The Shiny Trinket Maneouvre
dialogue: Sheldon, I’m the sole author on a paper being published in a distinguished journal that may change the course of my field.

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 12 – The Shiny Trinket Maneouvre
dialogue: Give me a minute. I’m gonna go wash up.

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 12 – The Shiny Trinket Maneouvre
dialogue: Hey.

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 12 – The Shiny Trinket Maneouvre
dialogue: What’s he doing here?

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 12 – The Shiny Trinket Maneouvre
dialogue: Well, I don’t want to talk to him. And I’m pretty disappointed in you, too. Although we both know that won’t last.

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 12 – The Shiny Trinket Maneouvre
dialogue: We both know that’s your koala face.

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 12 – The Shiny Trinket Maneouvre
dialogue: Jewellery? Seriously? Sheldon, you are the most shallow, self-centred person I have ever met. Do you really think another transparently manip..oh! It’s a tiara! A tiara! I have a tiara! Put it on me, put it on me, put it on me, put it on me, put it on me, put it on me, put it on me.

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 12 – The Shiny Trinket Maneouvre
dialogue: Of course I do, I’m a princess, and this is my tiara!
Which is why the more intelligent the monkey, the more faeces they fling.
Ooh!
Ooh!
How come you never invite Sheldon and me on a double date?
No.
You just can’t handle her raw sexuality, can you?
Maybe he’s dying. That would be so romantic.
Too bad. If he were, she could just throw him in bed and ride him right up until he flatlines.
Come on.
If he were dying, would you sleep with him?
Assuming he were dying of something that couldn’t be sexually transmitted. You know, like a spear wound to the head.
How do you know? Are you a doctor?
With a dead man.
Guess it’ll just be Sheldon and me going on a double date with Howard and Bernadette.
Me, too. Out of deference to them, let’s not flaunt our happy relationship.
Ooh!
If you and Leonard get back together, Sheldon and I will finally have someone to go on double dates with.
Fine, we can double with you, too. So insecure.
Penny?
Penny?

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 14 – The Beta Test Initiation
dialogue: Hang on, Dr. C. What’s vexillology?

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 14 – The Beta Test Initiation
dialogue: Cool. I think I just learned something.

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 14 – The Beta Test Initiation
dialogue: I’ll say.

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 14 – The Beta Test Initiation
dialogue: Sweet!

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 14 – The Beta Test Initiation
dialogue: I’m surrendering to fun.

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 14 – The Beta Test Initiation
dialogue: You okay?

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 14 – The Beta Test Initiation
dialogue: Hang on, Dr. Cooper. What’s vexillology?

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 14 – The Beta Test Initiation
dialogue: It’s Ferdinand T. Flag. I thought he might help bring in some younger viewers.

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 14 – The Beta Test Initiation
dialogue: For someone who has a machine that can travel anywhere in time and space, Doctor Who sure does have a thing for modern-day London.

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 14 – The Beta Test Initiation
dialogue: What’s baffling me is what you could’ve possibly put on the list. Hair too golden? Laugh too musical? World too much a better place for her mere presence in it?

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 14 – The Beta Test Initiation
dialogue: Her heart’s full of love, no one cares what’s in her mouth.

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 14 – The Beta Test Initiation
dialogue: Und ich bin eine pretzel!

episode_name: Series 05 Episode 14 – The Beta Test Initiation
dialogue: Mit…
I saved you a dumpling.
I’m sorry, Sheldon, I’m busy. I’m right in the middle of my addiction study. I’ve got a lab full of alcoholic monkeys, and tomorrow’s the day we switch them to O’Doul’s.
This is really happening. I’m gonna be a maid of honour. I’m gonna wear a beautiful dress and walk down that aisle and, finally, I will have my special day.
They’re gonna need an extra-large veil for somebody’s head.
Parental pressure can be daunting. I remember the battle with my mother about shaving my legs. Last year, I finally gave in and let her do it.

You know, the connection between marriage and money is nothing new. In fact, the term wed referred to the money and livestock that the groom paid the bride’s father. For example, you’re adorable, intelligent and a good earner. I could conservatively see you going for at least two oxen and a goose. (To Penny) You would fetch a unicorn.
I’m excited to work with my boyfriend. It’s gonna be romantic.

Come on, Sheldon. We can be like Marie Curie and her husband, Pierre, who spent their days working side by side, bathed in the glow of their love and the radium that ultimately killed her. Screw Beauty and the Beast, that’s the love story Disney should tell.
Oh, I’m gonna be doing some brain stem histology while you put yourself on the business end of a sponge and wash those beakers.
No, I just need those beakers washed. Hippity-hop, quick like a bunny.
Sheldon, you’ve never worked in a lab like this before. You have no experience in the field of biology.
Soap spots. Wash ’em again.
Sheldon, this beaker used to contain cerebral spinal fluid from an elephant that died of syphilis. If it’s, in fact, perfectly clean, drink from it.
All right, perhaps this task will be a little bit more up your alley. I need you to count the bacteria spores on these petri dishes.
I’m sure it was.
Yeah, good for you. Now, start counting.
How’s it going?
Great.
Really? Is that what you think?
Hey, I’ve been training in the field of neurobiology for 12 years. You’ve been here for three hours, and you’ve spent one of them in the bathroom.
Sheldon, I’ve given you the simplest things to do, and you haven’t done one of them right.
Maybe the math was too bubbly for him.
Okay, smart guy. I’m about to remove the locus coeruleus, which is incredibly delicate work. Have at it.
You’re getting warmer, it is, indeed, in the brain. Hope your hands are steady. It’s the width of a single hair. But this is just biology, so I’m sure it’s no problem for a genius like you.
Oh, are we nervous, Dr. Cooper?
No. But your thumb does.
Yeah, you’re a biologist.
What do you want?
Do you honestly think you can just waltz back in here after the way you behaved yesterday?
That’s not an apology.
I want a real apology.
No.
No.
Sheldon.
You’re forgiven. Now, if you want to stay, get started on those beakers. They’re still dirty from yesterday.
I got you a little something.
What’s huge is what you’ve done for me.

No, no, before I met you, I was a mousy wallflower. But look at me now. I’m like some kind of downtown hipster party girl. With a posse, a boyfriend and a new lace bra that hooks in the front, of all things. Open it. Open it.
I wanted to get you something you didn’t have.
Do you like it?
So, uh, where are you gonna hang it?
No problem.
Oh, what a great movie.
My mother didn’t allow me to watch it. She was afraid it might encourage me to join a gang.
I guess I should get going, too. Good night, painting Penny. Good night, real Penny.
You don’t have to say good night to painting Amy, ’cause she’s never leaving.
Thank you. Wait. Where’d the painting go?
Why?
You hate it.
I feel like an idiot.
Why? So you can just take it down when I leave? I don’t need your pity.
I’m just glad I didn’t go for the sculpture.
Don’t bother.
I’m so humiliated. I sat there the whole time that we were watching Grease, thinking you liked the painting.
I was a fool from Summer Lovin’ to the very last rama lama lama ke ding a de dinga a dong.
Yes, too much. Because our friendship is fundamentally asymmetrical. I clearly like you more than you like me.
I bought you a painting that’s 12 square feet in area. There’s a number.
If you don’t like feet, you can try dollars. The painting set me back three grand.
I’m sorry, I’m just having trouble believing you right now.
No. Damage is done.
Oh, my goodness, how could I have not seen that? The painting is a constant reminder that of the three of us, she is the least cool.
You have such a good heart.
Come on.
We’re going to go put this painting back up in your apartment.
Oh, screw her. She’s just lucky we let her hang out with us.
Little higher on the right.
Little more. No. That’s got it.
I’ll let you in on a little secret.
Originally we were painted nude. But I had him add clothes, ’cause I thought it was an unnecessary challenge to our heterosexuality.
But if you ever change your mind, all it would take is some warm, soapy water and a couple of sponges.
Sure.
I’m a cowboy, on a steel horse I ride. I’m wanted… I’m wanted… wanted, dead or alive. Sheldon, you’re ruining girlfriend-boyfriend sing-along night.
What about Supercuts?
Well, this isn’t a crisis. Why don’t you just let your hair grow out a little?

Well, I don’t know. I think you might look sexy with long hair. The kind that flows down to your shoulders and blows back while riding on a horse, bareback and bare-chested. I’m gonna go brush my teeth, it might take a while.
He showed up in the middle of the night with his bongos. I foolishly thought it was some sort of musical booty call.
That was kind of uncalled for.
There’s not a hair on my body I wouldn’t let this woman trim.
There’s only so many times a woman can say how about the bed?
Gentlemen, as much as I’m sure Sheldon would enjoy playing intergalactic make-believe, he and I have other plans. We are attending my Aunt Flora’s 93rd birthday party.
She’ll be disappointed if we don’t show up.

No, hang on. I followed all the protocols set forth by you in the relationship agreement. I made a written record request 72 hours in advance. I checked the tyre pressure on the car. I even contacted the Centres For Disease Control to find out what shots they recommend for travel to Orange County. FYI, it’s none.
You use it to get your way.
You gave me your word. You’re coming with me.
Good morning.

I think you’re really going to enjoy yourself today. Not only do you get to meet my relatives, but since my aunt’s nursing home is catering the party, all of the food is incredibly soft. It’s like a vacation for your teeth.
You sure you’re okay with this?
Thank you. That means a lot to me.
Sheldon, my relatives are going to want to talk to you, and you’re going to be sitting there playing a game? Isn’t that a little rude?

You know, if playing that game is more important to you than honouring your commitment to me, and you don’t mind me showing up at a party all by myself after I’ve already told everybody I’ll be bringing somebody, then, fine. Go home and play your game.
My boyfriend’s a jerk.
I had to go to my aunt’s party all by myself, and everybody was like, where’s this boyfriend you’re always talking about? Is he real, or did you make him up like Armin the miniature horse breeder?
The pretend boyfriend I invented to get my family off my back. It unravelled quickly when I couldn’t answer the question how’d you two meet?
Oh, that’s good.
I panicked and said Woodstock. I just wanted to show Sheldon off to my family.
Not just my first boyfriend, he’s the best boyfriend. I mean, think about it. I’m dating Sheldon Cooper.
He’s handsome, he’s lanky, he’s brilliant, and his skin has that pale, waxy quality.
Yeah.
Do you ever worry about Leonard doing that to you?
I don’t think I want to play a game.
Like that?
Spent a lot of my childhood throwing coins into wishing wells hoping for friends. At a certain point, you start doing trick shots just to keep things interesting.
That’d be my boyfriend. Happier playing his dopey Star Trek game with his friends than hanging out with me.
What?
What’s the difference?
How do I get him to treat me better?
No, he loves that.
Our record for sitting in a room together and not speaking to each other is six-and-a half hours. He said it was a magical evening.
I don’t think I’d be good at that.
I’m gonna publicly shame you, and then sit back as societal pressure compels you to modify your behaviour.
And if you don’t start treating me better, I’m leaving you for a miniature horse breeder named Armin.
Armin… damn it.
You’re hurting me.
Before; now it’s you.
Ooh, Science Center. Redeeming. Let’s go.
What about the Science Center?
Rain check.
All right, pivoting to the big question. Bernadette, on your wedding night you’ll be consummating your marriage. What do you think your first sexual position will be as husband and wife?
Keeping in mind that whoever’s on top may set the tone for the marriage.
Hey, they may conceive a child on their wedding night. Don’t you think the kid might get a kick out of knowing how it happened?
No, it’s not. I’ll explain it to you later.
I’m curious what’s bothering you most, the borderline incest, the prostitute or group sex with the girl dressed as the children’s cartoon?
Right. And that was…
I don’t think that was helpful.
Perhaps you should give him a taste of his own medicine. Do you have a cousin who you find attractive?
Hey, you introduced him to the sleazebag. I’m just trying to clean up your mess.
Oh, thank God. I’m still a maid of honour. (Joins in the hug)
This is kind of hot.
Seven o’clock, right on time.
Well, dinner’s almost ready.
Tempting choices, but I have something special planned for tonight.
With our friends moving forward in their relationships, I’ve decided that we should make progress in ours as well.
I had a feeling you’d be reluctant, which is why I’m going to dip into my neurobiological bag of tricks.
I have devised an experiment that I believe will increase your feelings for me in an accelerated time frame.
Human beings form emotional attachments as they grow up. In your case, to your mother, superheroes, et cetera. I’m going to attempt an experiment that will get you to transfer those feelings to me.
We’ll see. Let’s start with a little romantic dinner music, shall we?
Yes.
Fine. There’s no reason we still can’t have a lovely dinner. Why don’t you have a seat.
May I offer you something to drink?
Not even strawberry Quik?
Oh, I know. I think it will go nicely with what I have prepared for dinner.
Just like your mommy used to make.
Hello, Leonard.
We’re playing doctor. Star Trek style.
I love his eidetic memory, it’s so sexy. Sheldon, what are the ingredients in Pringles?
The uterus quivers, does it not?
No, no, no, this is not the wedding I wanted! I want to wear my maid of honour dress and walk down the aisle with a hundred eyes on me, while a string quartet plays The Way You Look Tonight.
Well, it was going to be mine.
Can I wear my maid of honour dress?
It’s all I have left. You’re going to take that from me, too?
I know.
Look at all these people in love. It kind of gets you thinking, doesn’t it?
All right, that’s enough. Today is not about you two. Today is about Howard and Bernadette and me.
Excuse me, I’m going to go see if the couple at the front of the line needs a maid of honour.
Oh, my gosh. I can’t believe my maid of honour dress is going to be on Google Earth.
Who is it?
Can’t come in. Bad luck to see the bride.
All right, that’s enough from the both of you.
Well, I’m ending it. Bernadette, I want to thank you for allowing me to be your maid of honour. I also want you to know, that I will be happy to do it again if this marriage craps out.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: This is so exciting. Soon, my upper lip will be the same fake blonde as my beautiful best friend.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: Oh, yes. According to the Relationship Agreement, on the anniversary of our first date, he must take me to a nice dinner, ask about my day and engage in casual physical contact that a disinterested onlooker might mistake for intimacy.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: How long does this stay on?

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: Once in high school, but I dozed off and woke up with second-degree chemical burns on my face.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: No, I had a cover story, I told everyone it was herpes. So, how’s everything going with you and Leonard?

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: Oh, boo-hoo. If Sheldon proposed to me during sex, my ovaries would grab on to him and never let go.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: Sheldon, this place is so romantic.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: Well, when you see him, tell him I say thank you.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: I don’t understand. What’s he doing here?

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: On our date? Sheldon, that’s not okay.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: You found a loophole?

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: I can’t believe I bleached my moustache for this.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: Go home.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: Sheldon, how could you do this? It’s our second anniversary.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: Thank you.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: Have I ever told you you’re like a sexy praying mantis?

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: You know what’s wonderful about the praying mantis? They devour their mate.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: Dessert is served.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: You know what? I’m done with this.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: I’m leaving.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: You do?

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: Sheldon, you either say something meaningful and from the heart, or you and I are done.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: Sheldon, that was beautiful.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 01 – The Date Night Variable
dialogue: I’ll take it.
That’s from Sheldon. He told me he had it engraved.
When I get married I’m going to register at the UCLA Cadaver Lab.
‘Cause I’ve always wanted a whole human skeleton and they are really spendy.
Not just someday. In exactly four years. But don’t tell Sheldon. He’s still a flight risk.
You’re not answering the question. Do you love him?
What does that mean?
Can’t help ya, kid. Whenever I’m around Sheldon, I feel like my loins are on fire. In the good way. Not the urinary tract infection way.
Well, I like it.
Just watch the movie.
There might be a reason for that.
Penny said she’s not sure she wants to be Leonard’s girlfriend anymore.
So?
It’s complicated.
She’s not sure how she feels.
Regardless, don’t say anything to Leonard.
Yes, please, Penny will kill me.
Hello?
Hang on, please. Hello?
I know. She’s yelling at me right now.
You slept with him?
Well, if that’s all it takes, it’s a good thing you don’t have a dog.
It’s so cute when she tries.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: Oh, yeah. I’m a man-eater now.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: Oh, I don’t know. Looks like something used by Tinkerbell’s gynecologist.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: I’m going to video-chat Sheldon. If my new look leads to phone sex, I’m going to have to ask you to leave the room.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: Oh, hello. Who are you?

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: I’d like to speak to Sheldon.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: All right. Well, tell him Amy called.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: He knows my last name. I’m his girlfriend. We have a contract and everything. I’ll send you a PDF.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: Hmm, that’s weird.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: Sheldon told me he had a new assistant named Alex. He didn’t mention that Alex was a girl.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: You’re right. I don’t have to worry about Sheldon.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: It’s her I have to worry about.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: Oh, really? Look at this face (Sheldon’s picture on phone) How can any woman spend eight hours a day alone with this face and not fall in love with it?

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: I’m not suspicious. I just want to stop in, say hi to my boyfriend and meet his new assistant. (Throwing open Sheldon’s office door) Aha!

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: Hang on. (Rubs Sheldon’s telephone receiver under her armpit)

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: Isn’t it obvious? I’m spreading my scent to mark my territory.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: Really? Because just before you became my best friend, I did this all over your apartment.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: Look at you, putting on a brave face.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: Really? I don’t know how much you know about primate behaviour, but Sheldon’s assistant was clearly courting Leonard. Were she a mandrill, she would have bent over and displayed her brightly coloured hindquarters like a big red welcome mat. By the way, you try that at the junior prom, you get kicked out.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: So says your prefrontal cortex. But meanwhile, the limbic system of your brain is calculating that if another woman is attracted to Leonard, it must be because he’s desirable.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: So it does bother you.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 03 – The Higgs Boson Observation
dialogue: And there you have it, prefrontal cortex reasoning versus limbic lust. If this were a boxing match, they might call it the thrilla adjacent to the amygdala. If you were a brain scientist, you would be busting a gut right now.
Me, too. But we’ll see him tomorrow.
Uh, box? Uh, window?
Uh, gift? Uh, Present!
Yes.
Penny, aren’t you gonna draw something?
Now?
Uh, hand. Uh, nail, polish?
Why don’t we do something athletic like go over to the university pool and play water polo?
All right, let’s keep it simple. How about darts?
We could go to the cadaver lab at UCLA and play real-life Operation.
Are you sure? I mean, the nose doesn’t light up, but if the corpse is fresh enough, sometimes you can get the leg to jerk.
Oh, there he is, I got him.
Long division, long division. Go, go, go.
Yes.
Ready, set, wrestle. (Penny pins Sheldon straight away) One, two, three, pin.
On the count of three. One, two…
One, two, three, eat.
Ladies night at the Cheesecake Factory. Does it get any better than this?
Question. Do you think your husband’s fondness for turtlenecks is an expression of longing for his missing foreskin?
And my boyfriend?
Then what’s your job?
That’s not always true. Last night I gave Sheldon my best come-hither look, and he responded by explaining how wheat came to be cultivated.
Why?
He takes hypotheses and designs protocols to determine their accuracy.
I think I’m gonna try green tea mixed with lemon zinger.
So, listen, Sheldon, I was thinking, since this is gonna be our first Halloween party as boyfriend and girlfriend, I thought it might be fun for us to go in a couples costume.
Really? I find that inconsistent with everything I know about you.
Yeah?
Sheldon, when I said couples costume, I meant like Romeo and Juliet or Cinderella and Prince Charming, not two robots from some silly movie I don’t even like.
I make compromises for you all the time. Just this once, can’t we find something that we’re both happy with?
You know salt makes me retain water and my cousin William was ground to death in a pepper factory accident. How about Raggedy Ann and Andy? I loved them growing up.
No. There are certain things that say to the world, I have a boyfriend, and he’s not made up. Matching costumes, hickeys and sex tapes. Pick one.
Sheldon, get in here.
I’m Raggedy Ann, and he’s Raggedy C-3PO.
I once looked in Sheldon’s underwear drawer. He yelled at me. But now I know what it looks like and he can never take that away.
Not to mention, your acting career is going south like Sherman. Read about it in your book.
Why wouldn’t you tell Leonard?
You guys have got to be the weirdest couple I know.
I can, but she’s sitting right there.
Wow, my boyfriend is friends with Stephen Hawking and my new dandruff shampoo doesn’t smell like tar. Everything really is coming up Amy.
You know, when one male dominates another, his testosterone level rises.
It’s exciting to think you might be getting a testosterone level.
Oh, you could turn his act into extract (pronounced with emphasis on act), and it would be for double points.
Sorry.
How’d it go with Leonard?
Understood.
You’re smart.
I feel like I’m in high school again.
I know. It’s finally working.
Cut.
Sorry, Sheldon, you were brilliant as always. Wil, that was a little wooden.
Don’t worry, it wasn’t terrible. Just, this time, try to say it the way people sound. And action.
Cut.

dialogue: This is so exciting. I’m feeling all tingly. Although that could just be my newly defoliated bikini zone.

dialogue: In Sheldon’s spot.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 09 – The Parking Spot Escalation
dialogue: Don’t play dumb with me, sister. You tell your husband he owes me two hundred dollars.

dialogue: You?

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 09 – The Parking Spot Escalation
dialogue: Oh, my God,

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 09 – The Parking Spot Escalation

dialogue: You had my car towed.

dialogue: I think I’m too sick to go to the funeral.

dialogue: Sheldon, aren’t you gonna take care of me?

dialogue: Never mind. Good night, Sheldon.

dialogue: Thank you, Sheldon.

dialogue: Sheldon, you don’t get over the flu in half an hour.

dialogue: Maybe we should start with that.

dialogue: Okay, okay, here’s the deal. I don’t need your medicine. I’m not sick.

It is, isn’t it?
I do. And don’t worry, someday you’ll have somebody, too.

Yes.

Yeah?

Sheldon, what’s going on?

dialogue: Hmm. We doing just Disney or California Adventure, too?

Sheldon!

dialogue: You don’t have to come in here and cheer me up.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 23 – The Love Spell Potential
dialogue: I’ll tell you what they think. They think our relationship is a joke.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 23 – The Love Spell Potential
dialogue: Sheldon, are we ever going to have an intimate relationship?

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 23 – The Love Spell Potential
dialogue: And now?

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 23 – The Love Spell Potential
dialogue: Do you have any interest now?

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 23 – The Love Spell Potential
dialogue: Wow. Talk dirty to me.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 23 – The Love Spell Potential
dialogue: I guess I know that. It’s just, part of me wants more.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 23 – The Love Spell Potential
dialogue: Come on. Let’s go back out there.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 23 – The Love Spell Potential
dialogue: Okay.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 23 – The Love Spell Potential
dialogue: Oh.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 23 – The Love Spell Potential
dialogue: I kiss you on the lips.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 23 – The Love Spell Potential
dialogue: I remove your armour. What do you do?

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 23 – The Love Spell Potential
dialogue: Keep rolling.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 23 – The Love Spell Potential
dialogue: Go away! Sheldon is nibbling on my (sound of dice) 14! Yes!

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 24 – The Bon Voyage Reaction
dialogue: Hello, Rajesh.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 24 – The Bon Voyage Reaction
dialogue: And now he can talk. I want to cut open your brain and see what the heck’s going on in there.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 24 – The Bon Voyage Reaction
dialogue: It should be me.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 24 – The Bon Voyage Reaction
dialogue: A, that was not a joke, that was a sincere request. And B, more importantly, I was the outsider to this group, and I know how frightening that can be. But you guys took me in and made me feel loved, like I was family.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 24 – The Bon Voyage Reaction
dialogue: So, after I started dating Sheldon, I met Leonard, and then everybody else, and they’ve all been so wonderful to me.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 24 – The Bon Voyage Reaction
dialogue: Maybe next week, we could all get together.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 24 – The Bon Voyage Reaction
dialogue: Ignore him. He’s a little nervous ’cause he doesn’t think I understand the severity of your social anxiety.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 24 – The Bon Voyage Reaction
dialogue: Excuse me, but I’m a neurobiologist. I think I’m a little more qualified than you to understand what’s not working in your girlfriend’s brain!

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 24 – The Bon Voyage Reaction
dialogue: Rajesh, I thought Lucy was coming.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 24 – The Bon Voyage Reaction
dialogue: Me, too.

episode_name: Series 06 Episode 24 – The Bon Voyage Reaction
dialogue: Does he ever shut up?
Because I looked in the bed, and there are no bugs.
Good night. No, I will not consider sleeping in my garment bag.
Oh, brain lesions are fascinating. Unless they’re yours, then they’re a drag.
And to the sick and dying who make it possible.
Which is fine, but it’s nice to mix it up with a little intellectual conversation.
Oh, my gosh, boys bought us drinks, boys bought us drinks. Thank you, thank you, thank you so much.
You be cool. Guys are hitting on us, and not just to get to Penny.
So what happened? How’d it go?
So I can drink this without having to give up the goodies?
And why would no one blame me?
Well, it sounds like you’re saying that I could do better than Sheldon.
No, tell me, I want to know what you meant by that.
And your husband is extremely Howard. What’s your point?
We could, but unfortunately my brain is lesion-free and I remember that rotten thing you just said about my sweet baboo.
Sure.
Your husband’s weird and his clothes are ridiculous.
Mm-hmm. It was rather flattering to have strangers send us drinks.
Maybe tomorrow morning we put on some hot pants and see if we can score us some free omelettes.
I think I would have gone with the short one with the goofy haircut.
Not my guy. I caught him staring at my rack. It’d be nice to be with a man who wants to know what’s underneath my cardigan. FYI, it’s another cardigan.
Your brainy virgin kind of sounds like Sheldon.

Oh, and here’s a fun thing. I worked it out so that there are two different words for spoon, planko and janko. Planko is a spoon with food, janko is a spoon without food. Janko is spelled with a silent ptang. Sheldon, you’re not even listening to the rules of my made-up language.
Then what does tweepadock mean?
Lucky guess.
What happened?
What?
I don’t think Penny would cheat on Leonard.
You’re being ridiculous.
Poor Leonard.
Do you hear anything?
Is it Penny?
Yeah, like you know what kissing sounds like.
Let me listen. Sounds like Leonard.
No, Sheldon, don’t.
Please leave me out of this.
Hello, sailor.
Driving Sheldon to work.
Well, he’s mad at you, too. He says you’re the succubus who led his friend astray.
Sheldon, your fight’s with Leonard. Penny’s got nothing to do…
Really?
You want to take the bus to work?
FYI, I had a doughnut for breakfast, you jerk.
We’re sorry, Rajesh.
Scavenger hunts at Harvard were really tough. I always got stuck on the first challenge, trying to find someone to be on a team with me. I guess that story’s more sad than funny.
Yeah, me, too.
Stop that. Penny is not a liability.
Maybe we pick names out of a hat.
I did them all the time as a kid. As my mom used to say, when you’re doing a puzzle, it’s like having a thousand friends. She was full of fun lies like that.
I’m sorry you got stuck with me. I bet you wanted to be with Bernadette.
No.
I think this is the first time we’ve ever actually been alone together.
Well, off the top of my head, I’d say we don’t have a lot in common except for the people we’re involved with. Plus, when we first met, Penny warned me never to get into a car alone with you.
Such as?
Uh, let’s see. I like harps, Little House on the Prairie, medieval poetry, medieval literature…
Great. Sheldon never lets me listen to music in the car. He doesn’t want to be mistaken for a gang member.
Beatles, boring. Eminem, scary. Weird Al? How old are you? Neil Diamond?
I love Neil Diamond.
Yes, it’s not a ruse to make fun of me. It’s a real game and I’m winning it.
Oh, oh, that’s good. Then this would be (whispers back)
To the Neil Mobile.
They’re coming to America.
They’re coming to America… ♪
Today!
Ain’t no big surprise.
And I’ll tell you some lies.
There’s a Neil Diamond concert next month.
She got the way to groove me.
She got the way to move me, honey.
It was good.
I enjoyed it. When you told me I was going to be losing my virginity, I didn’t think you meant showing me Raiders of the Lost Ark for the first time.
It was very entertaining despite the glaring story problem.
All right. Indiana Jones plays no role in the outcome of the story. If he weren’t in the film, it would turn out exactly the same.
No, I do, and if he weren’t in the movie, the Nazis would have still found the ark, taken it to the island, opened it up and all died, just like they did. Let me close that for ya.
Well, the last time you made an unscheduled video-chat, there was a curly fry in your regular fries and you thought someone might be trying to slip you a mickey.
So what can I do for you?
Really?
That sounds lovely. Why are you rubbing your hands together?
Of course I’m in.
Good night, Dr. Cooper.
I love Little House. It made me want to live on a farm so much I tried to milk my cat. That tangy bowl of Cheerios was not worth the stitches.
You’re trying to get back at me for what I said about Raiders of the Lost Ark.
Sheldon, we’re in a relationship. When you get angry, just tell me. You don’t need to seek revenge.
Well, that’s not how we’re going to do it.
I shouldn’t have said it. I’m sorry.
Do you feel better?
It’s actually steamier than it looks. Sheldon’s looking up the phallic symbolism of root vegetables in Renaissance paintings.
Sheldon, I have some exciting news to tell you.
I’ve been invited to consult on an experiment at your university for a few months. Isn’t that great? We could have lunch together. We could carpool.
So, you’re okay with this?
Well, this project would have us working in close proximity to one another. And there’s the vulgar adage that one should not defecate where one eats.
Sheldon, don’t defecate where you eat means don’t have a romantic relationship in the workplace.
Yes.
I’m relieved that you don’t have a problem with us working together.
I’m leading a study to see if deficiency of the monoamine oxidase enzyme leads to paralyzing fear in monkeys.
Wait, you’ve, you’ve done this experiment on humans?
I don’t mind. I’m hoping to put his love of repetition to good use someday.
Sheldon. I already signed the contract. I cashed a cheque.
No, we’re not good here. I am working on this project.
Sheldon, you don’t have to worry about me bothering you. I’ll be in a different building. And we don’t even have to have lunch together.
Yes. Before all things, I’m a scientist. I’m just there to do my work and, with a little luck, scare the living crap out of some monkeys.
More and more sure.
I didn’t ask for your permission.
Gentlemen.
And this is Dr. Gunderson from Stockholm.
Where are we going with this, Dr. Cooper?
Sheldon.

Test subject D7, aka Betsy, fear response study. Image number one, Frenchman on bicycle carrying baguettes. No visible reaction. Image number two, sousaphone. Still no reaction. Okay. Let’s kick things up a notch. Image number three, crocodile with a mouthful of monkeys. Okay, now we’re talking.
What do you want, Sheldon?
Oh, sorry, sorry, sorry. Sorry, uh, better?
Determining baseline fear levels in capuchin monkeys by measuring their response to visual stimuli.
I can’t leave now, Sheldon. I’m very busy. Besides, why would I want to do you a favour after the way you treated me in the cafeteria? Image number four, boa constrictor.
You embarrassed me in front of my colleagues on my first day here. Image number five, kitten in a teacup.
You know what? I don’t have time for this. Find another way home.
Really? What tipped you off?
Get out.
Image number six, woman giving birth.
Sheldon, what are you doing here so late?
No.
What do you want?
Sheldon, you’re not a weirdo.
What’s your point?
I like you, too.
Sheldon, too. If I see him at work, I’m just going to ignore him.

Could be anything. Last time he was like this, he figured out electron transport in graphene. The time before that, he was making a list of who’s allowed in his tree fort if fe ever gets one. Still can’t believe I didn’t make the cut.
Oh, I love that.
I don’t think the Smithsonian’s gonna want your marker.
Sheldon, I’m so proud of you.
What’s next?
And what?
What’s wrong?
What are you talking about?
That Americans can’t handle the metric system?
But the Chinese team found the element.
So you just got lucky?
You and me both, brother. It doesn’t matter. The element was found because of you, and that’s groundbreaking.
You know, Sheldon, in neuroscience, we’re forever finding something in one part of the brain that we thought was someplace else.
I’m not.
Sheldon, I’ve been thinking about it, and you’re right. You don’t deserve any credit. All you did was misread some numbers on a table. A very easy table, too. Honestly, I’m embarrassed for you.
Poor Bernadette.
Sheldon, get over here.
Sheldon.
Shh.
Me? What did I do?
Sorry.
Oh, Sheldon.
Can’t talk, in the zone.
I’ve never seen him this happy before.
Yes, and I’ve heard so much about you. Hey look, we’re wearing the same orthopaedic shoes. I can’t believe I dress like a celebrity.
Sheldon, come on.
Is it really worth getting upset about?
Come on, he’s a retired kids show host.
Have you ever thought about why Arthur didn’t want you to read his paper?
Maybe he found you, um, a bit much.
From what I saw the other day, I could understand why he and some people might find you…
Doesn’t matter.
Sheldon.
This is fun. I’m going to feel like such a vixen wearing jewellery that doesn’t have a list of medications I’m allergic to.
How do you not know how to use glue? Did you ditch pre-school?
I’m making a bracelet.
Actually, I’d kind of like to try that.
Wow, Penny, good job.
What are you working on?
That’s sweet.
Hello.
So, what tools did you bring?
Rajesh, do you want to make a bracelet for your mom to go with the necklace?
They’re gonna have sex before Sheldon and I do, I know it.

episode_name: Series 07 Episode 08 – The Itchy Brain Simulation
dialogue: At work today, I did an in vivo stereotaxic surgery.

episode_name: Series 07 Episode 08 – The Itchy Brain Simulation
dialogue: Oh, my gosh. That’s the girl that broke Rajesh’s heart.

episode_name: Series 07 Episode 08 – The Itchy Brain Simulation
dialogue: We’re never getting our drinks.

episode_name: Series 07 Episode 08 – The Itchy Brain Simulation
dialogue: Not even close.

episode_name: Series 07 Episode 08 – The Itchy Brain Simulation
dialogue: You want to say sorry.

episode_name: Series 07 Episode 08 – The Itchy Brain Simulation
dialogue: You told Lucy he was a pathetic mess.

episode_name: Series 07 Episode 08 – The Itchy Brain Simulation
dialogue: I must say, Sheldon, you’re handling this DVD business with an impressive amount of maturity.

episode_name: Series 07 Episode 08 – The Itchy Brain Simulation
dialogue: Is there some kind of new coping mechanism you’re employing?

episode_name: Series 07 Episode 08 – The Itchy Brain Simulation
dialogue: I’m gonna go with sad. So what’s the story with you and this DVD?

episode_name: Series 07 Episode 08 – The Itchy Brain Simulation
dialogue: Seriously?

episode_name: Series 07 Episode 08 – The Itchy Brain Simulation
dialogue: I think the real question is, why do you waste your time with cheap, childish pranks?

episode_name: Series 07 Episode 08 – The Itchy Brain Simulation
dialogue: Sheldon, that was diabolical.
We do. And I expect you to be on your best behaviour.
Are you honestly comparing Thanksgiving dinner at Wolowitz’s mom’s with one of the greatest tragedies in the history of mankind?
They’re real.
No traffic, we’re sailing.
Sheldon, that’s completely inappropriate. You can’t keep comparing yourself to a slave.
It says here you can get an annulment if any of the following conditions are met. Were you unable to consummate the marriage?
Is there any evidence of fraud, bigamy, want of understanding?
Ding, ding, ding. We have a winner.
Happy Thanksgiving.
Sheldon.
You need any help?
Uh, sure.
Did you guys know Penny married Zack three years ago?
Ooh!
I can’t believe Penny’s married to Zack.
Broad shoulders, good hair.
I know how you feel. Sheldon ignored me for a week when he got that Roomba vacuum. I kick it when he’s not looking.
Zack’s here!
Ooh.
All right, mister, I think you owe Howard and Bernadette an apology.
Thank you.
Sheldon.
Yeah, everything was delicious.
I know you don’t like it, but every time you do an interview, it raises the profile of the university. That translates to funding.
Sheldon, can I come in?
No.
Sheldon, you said you were unhappy getting attention for something you wished you never did.
Sheldon, the point is Wil learned to embrace that part of his life and moved on to bigger and better things.
Uh, we’re trying to cheer him up, so…
Okay.
Sheldon, it’s a beautiful night. Why don’t you and I go for a nice walk together?
Thank you, Rajesh.
You should probably go.
A little early for alcohol, isn’t it?
I’ll get the vodka.
Well, I have an extremely low centre of gravity. I’m like a pyramid.
Right now? Why?
How come you never said she was pregnant?
Can I give you a ride to the airport?
Yeah, kinda.
That’s wonderful. So you’re at the hospital?
Oh, I love that movie.
It’s great. It’s Christmastime and Jimmy Stewart’s really depressed and he’s gonna jump off a bridge and kill himself.
You make jokes about Sheldon, but if it weren’t for him, I don’t think any of us would be sitting in this room right now.
It’s true. None of you would know me. You wouldn’t know Bernadette. You wouldn’t be dating Penny.

Which couldn’t have happened if you didn’t live across the hall from her, which couldn’t have happened without Sheldon. Same goes with you guys. If Leonard wasn’t with Penny, she never would have set you up.
Listen to me. That is not the way they usually look.
And with Leonard out of the picture, we all know what that would mean.
Where’d you go?
Here’s another one. Penny, if it weren’t for Sheldon you never would have met comic book legend Stan Lee.
Wait, did she die or did you kill her?
It’s hard to say, my life would be so different.
I don’t know.
Happy birthday to me, happy birthday to me, there’s tears in the frosting, happy birthday to me. (Stuart honks a party hooter at her.)
Yay.
Come on, Sheldon, you should go.
Well, you always complain that you never had an intelligent role model growing up, and now you can be one for your nephew.
If that were true, I wouldn’t still be living alone. Well, not exactly alone. I do have a 50 pound sack of rice with one of Sheldon’s T-shirts on it.
I wish I could believe you. I also wish there wasn’t a mouse living in Rice Sheldon.
I don’t understand.
Oh. Wow. I had no idea. He is so into me. Wait, wait, where’d I go?
I am in the mix. And I’m the hottest one.
That’s fine, she’s dead.
Just really glad you’re back.
I missed you.
Did you miss me?
Oh.
Did you hold the baby?
And? How did it make you feel?
This is nice, that we all get to eat together.
Hmm. Can we maybe put the phones down and have an actualhuman conversation?
Congratulations.
What’s the show?
He’s wrong.
Why?
Just think of the first 245 as the prequel.
Well, that makes sense. The prefrontal cortex is responsible for planning and anticipation, and patients with brain lesions on their…
Sheldon, you scared me. That wasn’t funny.

Okay, the notion that you can read a few books and come up with a definitive theory of comedy is absurd. I mean, humour is a complex neurological… (Sheldon drops his trousers) Okay, that’s pretty good.
I guess.
Sure.
I don’t think I want to go out with you anymore.
Sheldon, how many words are you gonna go through?
Hello.
He’s home trying to use science to determine the basis of humour.
It’s exhausting. Do you have any idea how hard it is to laugh at a knock-knock joke that starts with knock-knock-knock, Amy, knock-knock-knock, Amy, knock-knock-knock, Amy?
Hello, Mr. Rat Brain. Not so bitey without the rest of the rat to back us up now, are we?
Hey, what brings you guys here?
Why? Because Sheldon’s not here this week, and you don’t think I have any other options? I’m just kidding. I’ll get my purse.
That’s okay. Uh, Bert, this is Howard and Rajesh. Guys, this is Bert.
This is so pretty. Bert works for the geology department.
Oh, you forgot your quartz.
He’s nice.
What?! No, he doesn’t.
So? He does that every day. Oh.
He’s not my boyfriend.
Should someone as lonely as you really be making fun of me?
What do I do? I don’t want to hurt his feelings.
I guess it hasn’t come up.
I’m sorry. Who are you dating?
Penny really quit The Cheesecake Factory?
That’s nice.
Hello, Bert.
Listen, um, Bert, before you say anything else, I, I have a boyfriend.
Weren’t you?
That’s very nice of you, but I do have a boyfriend.
No, that’s not true. My boyfriend has an off-putting personality, too. Like, way worse than you.
Don’t say that.
No, Bert, come on. I’d love to go to the mineral show with you.
No, it’s not.
So what am I supposed to do now?
This isn’t funny. I’m gonna have to tell him the truth, that even if I didn’t have a boyfriend, I wouldn’t be interested in him.
Well, how would you want a girl to tell you she wasn’t interested?
Okay, I don’t have time for this. I’m just gonna go find him and be brutally honest.
Really? You would do that?
Thank you.
Last week, you spent that on a little dress.
Why can’t they do something sensible like Sheldon and start their own comic book convention? Also, who wants to throw me out that window?
Oh. You mean like a museum?
Ooh, afternoon tea, how sophisticated of us.
There sure are a lot of little kids here.
Well, last time I got dressed up and had tea was when I was five. Just me, my teddy bear, Raggedy Ann and my hamster.
It was. Till my hamster ate all her babies. It got less cute really fast.
Aw. Drinking in the afternoon, just like her mommy.
On the bright side, every six-year-old there was jealous of my tiara. Not gonna lie, it felt good.
Gosh.
I think I have you both beat. Imagine trying to feel like a grown-up when you’ve never even been with a man.
I told you it was Penny.
Maybe the guys are right. I mean, we spent the whole night trying to be mature, and it was kind of boring. I’m sure they’re having more fun than we are.
Item 28, your pet name for me. Time’s running out on this. You need to make a decision.
I’m sorry, but Gollum and Flakey are not acceptable.
We’ll come back to that one. This brings us to the final item in our annual State of the Relationship Summit. Item 29, Valentine’s Day.
Before you get upset, I believe I’ve come up with a way for us to celebrate the occasion that we both can enjoy.
I propose we spend a weekend at a bed-and-breakfast in Napa Valley.
Come on, Sheldon. Why not?
One step ahead of you, Bernadette and Wolowitz are going with us.
I got you your own room.
It doesn’t. I know it makes you feel like you’re bathing inside a monster.
We’re going to have Valentine’s Day dinner on a fully functioning vintage train.
An Alcoa FA-4 diesel locomotive leading a train of meticulously restored 1915 Pullman first-class coaches.
Well, an evening looking at the stars, that’s still kind of romantic.
I’m trying to put lipstick on a pig here. Work with me.
What do you think, Sheldon?
I’m so glad you like it.
Uh, I think we’re gonna need a minute.
See if you guys can guess this one. Bang. Splat. Thud.
Why do I even try?
It’s feeling like it never will.
Why? Because my boyfriend’s off playing choo-choo with some weirdo?
I don’t know what made me think tonight would be any different.
Okay. I need to speak to my boyfriend in private, like, right now.
Oh, give it a rest.
Why are you still here?
I’m being rude? You’ve been rude to me this entire evening.
Leave.
It’s Valentine’s Day. We’re supposed to be having a romantic weekend.
Fine, it’s true. I deserve romance, and I didn’t know how else to make it happen.
Sheldon.
That was nice.
Okay, have fun.
Really? I do.
Hey, you were funny on purpose, good job.
Yeah. You actually do have room for one up there.
I’m not surprised you want to end the relationship. I’m a little surprised you didn’t get AppleCare. Anyway, enjoy your life. Where do I sign?
Oh, I’ve already moved on. Besides, this breakup has nothing to do with me.
Of course not. This is just Leonard trying to take the focus off that dreadful table by sowing discord in our relationship. He’s manipulating you like he always does.
All the time. And he knew that, as your girlfriend, I wasn’t gonna stand by and let him bring a table into your apartment. I mean, a table? Come on?
Well, thankfully, I won’t have to see it, ’cause I won’t be your girlfriend anymore. Amy Farrah Fowler. Why, yes, I would like to take a survey.
Of course I was.
I think if I were manipulating you, you’d be smart enough to see it.
I think you’d be smart enough to see that, too.
Which you also figured out by yourself.
Which is stronger than ever.
You don’t need to explain yourself to him.
You’re sick of his nonsense and ready to move in with me.
Damn it, I got cocky.
Rajesh?
Can I borrow it when you’re done?
I think we’re gonna go.
I think we’re gonna go.
Really?
Thanks for walking me to my car.
Why can’t Raj find a girl? The mystery continues.
Whatever happened with your online dating?
Before I met Sheldon, I was ready to give up, too. Once, I even dropped in on my OBGYN just to get some human contact.
Then I met Sheldon and look at where we are now.
That’s true. Do whatever you want.
Oh. Let me guess. There’s an undergrad in a leather jacket snapping his fingers by the water fountain.
Oh, she’s cute. And smart. Phi Beta Kappa.
Great, so what do you need me for?
All right.
Wow.
No. You’re supposed to be yourself, not all desperate and creepy.
Just say something normal like, I saw your profile. Looks like we have a lot in common, let’s get a cup of coffee sometime.”
I’m not gonna pretend to be you.
Well, what would I say to her?
No. What’s up?
I have.
And I’m afraid she doesn’t think you’re right for her.
I told her what a good guy you are, but she thought it was a bad sign that you didn’t write to her yourself. She thought it made you seem too shy and passive.
Look, I’ll see if I can change her mind tomorrow night.
I’m meeting her for coffee.
Well, we just, we e-mailed back and forth a bit, and we kind of hit it off.
No. We just ended up having a lot in common. We went to Harvard, we like Chaucer, we’re both hardcore into quilting.

Look, I admit that it’s odd that Rajesh didn’t write to you himself, but if you get to know him, you’ll see he’s just a sweet, regular guy. As a counterpoint, here he is, uninvited and visibly sweaty.
Are we still going to go to that Chaucer reading Friday?
Should you really be sitting in Sheldon’s spot?
Oh, hi.
I don’t know.
I’m leaving.
Yeah, it’s Bloom.
I think it might be fun to be someone else tonight.
Oh, ugh.
According to Wikipedia, Sherlock Holmes came first.
Hey, I found something. It looks like a little man with a briefcase.
That is so sweet.
What’s it for?
But why?
Hey, I won the Nobel Prize in physiology, then I used the money to buy Stuart’s comic book store, and close it down so Sheldon would pay attention to me. Not the worst idea.
What does your card say, Bernadette?
Dun, dun, dun. He started it.
I’m surprised you guys never talked about this stuff.
Actually, our relationship agreement covers a wide array of scenarios, including career changes, financial instability, intelligent dog uprising. FYI, we plan on selling out the human race hard.
Excuse me?
It actually was kind of fun.
Yeah.
Of course.
I’m sure it’s lovable.
Okay.
Oh, my gosh.
No. No, it was a mistake.
Now I think you’re flirting with the line. Good news?
You’ll get offered something soon.
Maybe you’ll get hit by a car and die. LOL, right?
Can you get the butter, please?
Then get the other one. Pass the butter.
Fine, Sheldon. You have my undivided attention.
No way.
Well, you wouldn’t want your gaming system to overheat.
Included?
Why would they still be using DDR3? Are they nuts?
Whoa, whoa. Wait a second. Who’s they?
You’re kidding.
This is a nightmare. How will you ever make a decision?
Please pass the butter!
You’re welcome.
Uh, it’s date night. Aren’t you, uh, forgetting something?
No.
I’m proud of you, Sheldon.
Well, that’s got to be a good feeling.
Oh, crap.
