episode_name: Series 08 Episode 12 – The Space Probe Disintegration
dialogue: Basket weaving at the craft museum.

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 12 – The Space Probe Disintegration
dialogue: Are you crazy? You know he’s a flight risk.

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 12 – The Space Probe Disintegration
dialogue: Sheldon, that really is an excellent basket.

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 12 – The Space Probe Disintegration
dialogue: Very nice.
33 seconds. Okay, that’ll be our baseline.
It also gets its brain plucked out with tweezers.
All right, next, we’re gonna introduce an anxiety-inducing stimulus, measure your stress levels and see how it affects your problem-solving rate.
Ready? Begin. Why’d you pop it?
Look, I know you don’t like it, but that’s the point of the experiment. I need to irritate you to find your optimal anxiety zone. And you said no to tickling, polka music or watching me eat a banana.
My mother said that’s how good girls do it.
Sheldon, you’re a remarkable scientist. Just be patient, I’m sure you’ll find the breakthrough you’ve been looking for.
And if you only do solid research instead of making a groundbreaking discovery, what does it matter?
Look, your anxiety levels are right in the zone.
Because you’re happy they’re elevated.
That would be so romantic for you and Leonard.
If I were going to Hawaii, I’d spend all my time at the Keck Observatory. Did you know that the telescopes there have better resolution than the Hubble?
No, hold on. All canines instinctively know how to swim. Why wouldn’t a werewolf have the same abilities?
You’ve been working so much lately, I’m glad you didn’t forget about date night.
Sheldon.
Maybe you want to put the notebook away and talk to me.
Fine. How was your day?
Sheldon. Sheldon, I’m worried about you. You’re not eating, you haven’t slept in days, and, to be honest, that cap is starting to smell.
Sheldon, I want you to take that cap off.
I’m sorry, but you know we agreed not to bring work to date night.
Sheldon, stop it, I’m not kidding. Take the cap off, and put the notebook away.
You don’t need to drive yourself crazy in order to be productive.
That’s not true.
Sheldon, this has to stop. You need to get some sleep and take care of yourself.
Your thoughts and ideas come from you, not from your anxiety.
It’s one thing to make yourself miserable, but you’re making everyone around you miserable, too. Now, I’m telling you for the last time, take the cap off.
Whatever happened to that ape movie you were in?
They have it.
Please?
Have you even seen it?
Careful. She’ll bite your fingers off.
What is it?
What?
I haven’t learned my lesson. Play it. Play it.
Play it again. Play it again.
Why? What did I do?
No, please don’t.
But it’s personal.
No.
It’s not about me and Sheldon. It’s about a young woman in the 1800s named Amelia, and the time-traveling physicist named Cooper she falls in love with.
No.
Good luck finding it.
You know, there was a time when I was alone and had no friends. I’m starting to miss that.
He’s like that in the beginning, so she can change him. It’s called good writing. And wishful thinking.
In the 1800s that was considered flirting.
Okay, that’s enough.
You’re just making fun of me.

Fine. As Cooper prepared to depart, tears filled Amelia’s eyes. He took her hand in his and said, “I can’t stay, but I will never forget you.” He brushed his fingers against her cheek, then quickly stepped into the machine. “Please don’t go,” she whispered. But it was too late. The engine hummed to life.
She turned away, wiping her eyes. She couldn’t bear to watch her one chance at true love disappear forever. Then she felt a strong hand on her shoulder spin her around. It was Cooper.
“What about the future?” asked Amelia. He looked deeply into her eyes and whispered, “There is no future without you.” He pulled her in close. She began to tremble all over. She felt his warm breath…

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: Sure.

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: How many?

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: Is that really true?

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: What’s this for?

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: Well, that’s fascinating. I can’t wait to read it.

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: Well, I’d been thinking about a cellular automata approach to neuronal connectivity, and I thought it might have some interesting applications to string theory, it’s not a big deal.

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: I did. You said the only math biologists know is if you have three frogs and one hops away, that leaves two frogs.

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: Sheldon, we’re all scientists. I helped out a fellow colleague. You’re being petty.

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: Sheldon, it’s me.

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: What are you talking about?

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: Sheldon, open the door.

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: I just saw you.

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: Oh, hey.

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: It’s not a big deal. I run tests like this on undergrads all the time. If you fill out some paperwork at the university, I can get you five dollars.

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: So what are we talking, like, ten bucks?

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: Wow, the store looks great.

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: That’s not true.

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: Well, except Barnabas, but he was on Adderall.

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: How can I make this up to you?

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: One of us would have taken you in.

episode_name: Series 08 Episode 15 – The Comic Book Store Regeneration
dialogue: She did that to me, too.
I just read about an experiment designed to see if you could make two people fall in love in a matter of hours.
And then they finish it off by staring into each other’s eyes for four minutes.
Other than the fact that I had it, that was a magical night.
No.
Forget it.
That’s what I said. Before I knew it, he pontificated his way right into my heart.
Why?
I think we’re safe.
The two of us could do it.
What’s the first question?
Oh, then I choose a janitor, ’cause I’m about to throw up.
Sounds good.
Did he say anything about the funeral?
Well, we’re the ones tagging along, you pick.
Oh.
So, how do we start?
Keep it down, we’re working here.
We used the coordinates to locate the cities.
Well, if I don’t have a brother, my father’s son is me. And if I’m this man’s father, then he’s my son. The answer’s son.
So, that’s the key to the door? That’s it?
Well, to be fair, we do all have advanced degrees.
We have some exciting news.
After a careful evaluation of our relationship, we decided that the time was right to take a step forward.
Let’s say it together.
Yes.
Thank you. Acquiring a joint pet is a big step for us.
For Halloween, we can dress him as a cobblestone.
That’s what I said.
It’s okay. You made it. We’re fine.
Let’s forget about them, and pick ourselves out a nice turtle. Oh, how about this one up on the log?
Well, he’s barely moving. He looks half dead.
But that’s not your fault. Like you, we’re taking it ridiculously slow. You’ll stay with me when he’s at Comic-Con or away for work.
What are you talking about?
You applied for a mission to be a colonist on another planet, and couldn’t be bothered to tell me?
Of course not.
No one told you to poke the turtle’s face.
I’m surprised you even care if he likes you, since you’re planning on leaving the planet the first chance you get.
Sheldon, I know the odds of you even going to Mars are incredibly small, but it still hurts that you would volunteer for something that would take you away from me forever.
I would at least mention it before filling out the application.
And who says you could even survive an interplanetary mission, anyway? You could barely survive a tiny turtle bite.
You know what? Go to Mars, Sheldon.
No. Forget it.
Please don’t.
Why do you even want to do this?
Can’t you just tell me?
I think I’m gonna go home.

You know, Sheldon, at any other time, learning that you had plans to go live on Mars would be a slow news day. But a couple of hours ago, we were getting a turtle. And silly as it sounds, I thought that meant something.
Sure. Unless something better comes along.
What I want is for us to be planning our future together.
We’re on the same planet.
Are you asking me to go to Mars with you?
Okay. I suppose being the first people on a new planet would be incredibly exciting.
You know, we could also be the first people to procreate on Mars.
Think about it. If we had a family there, our kids would be Martians.
I guess we’ll have to make a new video together, as a couple.
I’d say I’m sorry I asked, except I didn’t.
Oh, let me see.
Sheldon, this article doesn’t mention Leonard at all.
It only refers to Dr. Cooper and his team. Did you even talk about him?
Poor Leonard.
He might not be.
Think about it. How would you feel if you were referred to as part of Leonard’s team?
So you see what I’m getting at?
No.
Try again.
Leonard is as much a part of this paper as you are, and he was overlooked. He’s going to feel bad.
Remember that time you didn’t get picked to pull the sword out of the stone at Disneyland and they let that other kid do it?
Exactly.
Well, that is an important part.
But Leonard’s idea was good.
It’s not your fault.
Not your fault.
Hey, look at that pretty bird.
Do you need any help in the kitchen?
Yes, so please behave yourselves.
All these bright people sitting around a table by candlelight. Feels like we could be an 18th century French salon.
Sheldon, The View is a daytime talk show hosted by women.
Ooh, please do, Rajesh.
We won’t know if there’s equality until female Thor has a baby and the Avengers are cool with her pumping breast milk at work.
Sheldon.
And girls.
I don’t hear it.
Who cares? Did they mention Leonard?
Are you all set for your trip?
Yes, who do you think gave him the danger whistle?
Can I be in charge of pricing? I’ve been going to garage sales my whole life. Can you believe I got these pantyhose for a nickel?
I had a table, too, but I didn’t have any friends, so all I did was serve.
And if I had a friend, they might have told me that.
Have you made a decision about the TARDIS? I think I can sell it if we call it Big British Porta-Potty.
Ooh, you just chose champions. It’s like we’re re-enacting the ancient German practice of trial by combat.
If you still have that bra, I’ll give you a nickel for it.
Rajesh eight, Penny four.
Eight-five.
Uh, it, it’s been a long time. I don’t know. I’m probably pretty rusty.
That’s not nice.
Well, that was an exciting 40 seconds.
Keep talking.
Really should have thought this through.
Can you please pass the salt?
Is this how the rest of the night’s going to be?
No, Sheldon.
According to the codicil of the Relationship Agreement which you insisted upon, we’re not allowed to pout or be moody on date night.
Well, it applies to you, too.
Probably not. It’s an evolutionary advantage to be included in group activities.
Being left out is a terrible feeling. No one understands that better than I do.
When there was a lice epidemic at my school, everybody got it except me. I tried to fool everyone by sprinkling sugar in my hair, but I just got attacked by bees.
And at the same time, not.
You know, there’s nothing I can do about getting you invited to the symposium, but if you wanted, we could build a fort.
More juvenile than this?
How’s it going, Sheldon?
Can I come in?
Amazing.
What are we doing? This is a fort. Let’s sit on the floor.
I’d say, Knox over Ticonderoga, ’cause it’s got the gold.
And McBlanket over Sumter ’cause it has a higher thread count. Oh. Ten o’clock. Date night’s over.
We both know this one’s gonna win.
Come on, I’ll help you take this down.
Well, as long as we’re suspending the parameters, I could stay really late and we could have our first sleepover.
It’s a big fort.
PG. Some scenes may be too intense for younger viewers.
You got yourself a sleepover.
Would it alarm you to know that I hid those things here two years ago just in case this ever came up?
Who says this is the only one I hid?
Yes, they are.
Okay, have a seat on the floor.
I can’t believe you got up and walked out of an audition for a big movie.
And you probably have to invite your other friend ’cause she overheard you talking about it, and it would be awkward to exclude her.
Leonard, have you ever given a high school commencement speech before?
I think it’s really nice that you’re sharing this experience with Penny.
With a beautiful girl on your arm.
It’s so nice both of your moms are coming in to see you guys get an award.
Sure, his mom gets roses. When I want them, they’re a bouquet of severed plant genitals.
He’s right. Roses die, but a moist rotting log will pump out mushrooms for two or three magical years.
Do you think the moms will get along?
Can you believe it’s been five years since our first date?
That’s what you’re thinking about?
Are any of them me?
What are you doing?
I didn’t kill anything. You did, talking about your stupid TV show.

Really? That’s the commitment issue you’re wrestling with? Sheldon, do you understand the irony of your fixation on a man with super speed, while after five years all I can get out of you is a distracted make-out session on a couch?
Oh, sure, I’d love to.
I’ve been thinking about them, too, Sheldon. Being your girlfriend is so challenging. Emotionally, physically. I’ve been incredibly patient for years.
Okay, well, this isn’t easy to say, because I love you, but I need some time to take a step back and re-evaluate our situation.
I hope you understand.
Bye, Sheldon.
Not really. Can you come over?
Hold on. You’re getting married and you didn’t invite me?
Wow. Hope I can catch the bouquet from here.
Oh. What are you doing here?
Well, it’s only been 11 hours.
Sheldon, when I’m ready to talk, I’ll let you know.
Sure.
We’re not back together.
If you must know, I’m going to Howard and Bernadette’s to watch the wedding.
There’s no guy.
I’m not gonna be alone. I’ll be with my friends.
Maybe because the two of us being there would make them feel awkward.
Thank you for doing this.
We were together for so long, I honestly don’t know what I’m feeling.
Oh. What was her name?
Sheldon, you being here might not be making things better.
They didn’t invite everybody but you.Bernadette invited me, and Stuart lives here.
I said I needed time to think.
It’s because you’re not giving me any space to think.
You know what, Sheldon, you’ve made this really easy. You’re immature, you’re selfish, you just insulted me to my face. I don’t need any more time to think. We’re broken up.
Yeah.
Thank you.
I just hope I did the right thing.
Like you’re doing right now?
What do you want?
What baby?
I’m hanging up.
Sheldon, I am not doing Fun With Flags with you.
Because we’re broken up.
No one’s talking about Sonny and Cher.
Sheldon, this has to stop. I know it’s hard. It’s hard for me, too. But I’ve seen and talked to you more in the two days we’ve been broken up than in the last two months that we were together.
What are you doing here?
And you didn’t do your compulsive knocking ritual so I would open the door.
Just give me the box.
Fine. My old scarf.
You mean the night that I went ice-skating, and you stood at the rail googling the symptoms of hypothermia?
Whose bra is this?
It’s Penny’s.
Good-bye.
Anybody can make a mistake in a weak moment.
Come on, you know Leonard’s not like that.
That’s because you made him more confident.
I’m gonna kill him.
I don’t know what you were thinking, but take the video down now.
I only watched it because you e-mailed it to me with the subject line this is gonna make you mad.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: I know we’re not making a fuss, but in the spirit of bachelorette parties, I made cookies in the shape of male genitals.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: Thank you. The veins are gummy worms.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: I had extra dough.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: Boy, that was a long night for me.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: So, Penny, how’s married life?

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: Fine, I guess. I’ve been focusing on me. I was thinking about changing my wardrobe.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: But then I decided I don’t want to go changing who I am just because of some man.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: Actually, I was thinking of making one small change.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: Piercing my ears.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: My mom said pierced ears were for whores, pirates and genies.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: I know, but Sheldon had this clause in the Relationship Agreement forbidding cosmetic surgery unless it’s to look like a Klingon.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: Really? You have a piercing gun?

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: Oh, I don’t know.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: You’re right. I should probably let all of my Facebook friends know. Penny, I’m no longer in a relationship.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: Who?

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: Why?

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: How long do you think you can keep it from him?

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: That wasn’t so bad. Nice. Boy, if my mom could see me now, she’d lock me in the sin closet.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: Actually, the joke was on her. I could still see the TV through the slats.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: Well, it’s kind of sad that they don’t know. I mean, they love Leonard.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: Uh, well, actually, to be honest, I haven’t told her yet.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: I’m feeling a little dizzy from all the blood loss. I don’t know what you’re talking about.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: Easy for you to say. You never had to watch 60 Minutes like this.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: Oh, maybe later. Your pig dying made me sad. And a little hungry.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: Okay. Okay. Fine. Hi, Mom.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 03 – The Batchelor Party Corrosion
dialogue: You saw that, huh? Hi, Mom. How are you doing? Oh, good. How’s work? That’s nice. I’m fine. Hey, listen, I’ve been meaning to ask, how come Aunt Doe and Aunt Florence never got along?
I’m sure you’ll find somebody else.
I don’t know how to help you. You know, feelings are a part of life.
I don’t think that was the point of the movie.
There you go.
I can’t believe he ran my credit.
You really should’ve gone on the Internet and checked how long that kind of thing lives before you got one.
Hey, I know Sheldon’s quirky, but he’s also brilliant and insightful. I think calling him a weirdo is a little unfair.
Well, for starters, you might want to rethink some of this artwork. I mean, this woman’s actually on a leash like a dog.
Have you thought about advertising directly to females?
You can say it.
Do you not hear how creepy that sounds?

Stuart, believe it or not, I understand. You know, before I met Sheldon, I was alone for a really long time. I was so desperate for people to like me, when I met these guys, it took everything in my power to hide my insecurity.
Suddenly, the rabbit thing makes sense.
I don’t have much experience turning men down. It wasn’t so much fun.
Barry Kripke just asked me out.
Hi, how are you? I was wondering if you’d like to get a drink after work sometime.
I don’t know. I guess I assumed that I would eventually date other people, but this is happening so fast.
Well, I was hoping the next person I dated would be a little less like Sheldon.
I don’t know.
Oh, I don’t have to imagine it.
Hello.
Uh, Bernadette, you’re my ride.
How have you been?
How’d that go?
Well, actually, he, he already did.
I said no.
I didn’t know you were interested in dating.
Oh. Okay. Anyway, um, it’s nice to see you. You look good.
I’m not sure how I feel about this.
Uh, excuse me, can I have my phone back?
Okay, I’m starting to feel guilty. Aren’t we being a little mean?
Oh, um, give me that.
No, no, stop reading that.
No, it, it’s not like that.
Okay, it’s like that.
Because it’s new and weird and I’m just trying to figure it all out. And I knew if I told you guys I had been out with a few people that you’d get way too excited about it.
It’s going fine. It’s mostly just been meeting people for coffee.
Well, I don’t have much experience dating, so I decided it would be good for me to, you know, get out there a little.
Thank you.
Three.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: Okay. But I’m really stepping outside of my comfort zone here.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: Well, some people think the sexiest organ is the brain.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: Do you have any heels higher than this? He’s pretty tall.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: Well, I told you his name and that he’s tall. What more do you need?

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: Just a little peck on the lips.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: Fine. Um, he’s British. All right, that is a juicy one.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: To that new Italian place on Walnut.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: I’m gonna go look for other shoes.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: Well, I’m having a good time, too. If you don’t mind me asking, why did you and your wife split up?

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: Oh, I’m, I’m so sorry.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: No. I mean, to be completely honest, I’ve, I’ve only been in one long-term relationship.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: That’s a good question. After five years, it was just feeling like more work than it should be.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: No. He’s a theoretical physicist at Caltech.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: Um, used to be string theory, now it’s dark matter. But let’s not discuss Sheldon. Let’s get back to you.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: I’m trying not to. Do you know him?

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: Sure, why not?

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: Um about an hour and half.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: Yes. Yep. We were on a date. Very much like this one.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: What was the rest of your question?

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: Really? You-you want me to introduce you to my ex-boyfriend?

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: I have a DVD of that lecture.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: Not as a Valentine’s present, no.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: That’s, um, terrific. Listen, I’m, I’m kind of tired. Can we call it a night?

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: No, you’re not.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: Thank you.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: What are you guys doing here?

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: No. Pinch me.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: No problem. I’m really sorry about your car.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: Um, listen, you’re a really nice guy, but I just, I don’t think this is working out.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: I’m, I’m really sorry.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: There you go.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: Sure. Heh.

episode_name: Series 09 Episode 08 – The Mystery Date Observation
dialogue: Okay, get out.
No one can go with you?
Oh. Okay. Thank you.
Sheldon, I can tell you want to go, so if you’d be comfortable with it, maybe we could go as friends.
Well it is Thanksgiving in an aquarium cafeteria, so I’m gonna go out on a limb here and say yes. But if you mean between us, I think it’ll be fine.
See you then.
Did you know they served shellfish and eel at the very first Thanksgiving?
Hi. Ready for the aquarium?
If that makes you more comfortable.
No. You?
I might go visit my aunt next week.
No, the one in Bakersfield.
Are we done discussing the weather?
Sheldon. We’ve known each other a long time. We are perfectly capable of having a conversation without relying on a list off the Internet.
I don’t know. Just ask me whatever comes to mind.
Man, I walked right into that one.
No. It’s okay. If we’re friends, we should be able to talk about anything.
So, you had some questions about me seeing other people.
Go ahead.
